#==================================================================#
#         Working gitignore for Unity 4.6 -> current (5.1)         #
#==================================================================#
#   When cloning the repo, Unity may ask to rebuild its database   #
#   Let it do it. It will take some times to rebuild the           #
#   .meta files, but it saves a lot of space on the git repo       #
#   This file should be enough to allow                            #
#    multiple devs to work at the same time.    Â                   #
#   It won't upload personal settings.                             #
#   Just take care with .scene files, git can't parse them !       #
#==================================================================#

#=============================#
#=============================#
#      IGNORE LIST FILES      #
#=============================#
#=============================#


# =============== #
# Unity generated #
# =============== #
[Tt]emp/
[Oo]bj/
[Bb]uild
Library/
[Ww]ebGLBuild/
[Hh]tmlBuild/
[Ww]indowsBuild/
[Ll]inuxBuild/
sysinfo.txt
# Unity3D generated meta files
*.pidb.meta

# ===================================== #
# Visual Studio / MonoDevelop generated #
# ===================================== #
[Ee]xported[Oo]bj/
/*.booproj
/*.csproj
/*.pidb
/*.sln*
/*.suo
/*.unityproj
/*.user
/*.userprefs
/*.xaccproj
/*.xaccdata
.vs/

 
# ============ #
# OS generated #
# ============ #
.DS_Store*
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Icon?
ehthumbs.db
[Tt]humbs.db




